Package com.pb.sawdust.util.parsing

Provides classes relating to parsing objects.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Parser<I,O>
    The Parser interface is intended for use by classes which can take an input and transform (parse) it into an array of outputs.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayParser<I,O>
    The ArrayParser class provides a framework for writing a Parser which parses an array of a given type into an output.
    BinaryParser
    The BinaryParser class parses byte arrays into byte sub-arrays.
    DelimitedDataParser
    The DelimitedDataParser is used to read delimited text data.
    FixedWidthStringParser
    The FixedWidthStringParser class parses character arrays into Strings formed from character sub-arrays.
    ObjectArrayParser<I>
    The ObjectArrayParser class parses object arrays into object sub-arrays.

Package com.pb.sawdust.util.parsing Description

Provides classes relating to parsing objects. Often parsing refers to text, but the classes in this package extend the idea to include any transformation of one object type to another.
